## Current state

**IDE bridge (#517) IS landed** â€” `src/acp.rs:165-219` defines `IdeState { active_file, recent_files, selection, diagnostics }`, populated by `apply_ide_file_opened` / `apply_ide_file_closed` / `apply_ide_selection_changed` / `apply_ide_diagnostics` (acp.rs:226-330). The ACP server consumes `ide/*` notifications at acp.rs:613 and 807. So the blocker named in the issue body is partially resolved: the editor-side push exists.

**Coordinator (#507) Phase 1 landed** but `dispatch()` returns `NotImplemented`. `SubagentStart/Stop` hook events exist (`src/hooks/mod.rs:64-66, 95-96`) but are never fired by `subagent::run_subagent` (src/subagent.rs:950).

**Neither delta from this ticket is wired:**
- No grep hit for `ide_opened_file` or `<ide_opened_file` anywhere in `src/`.
- No grep hit for `task_notification` anywhere in `src/`.
- `src/context.rs` and `src/prompt.rs` do not consult `IdeState`.

Compact-boundary portion of #516 shipped in 339a872.

## Phase 2 spec â€” two small deltas

**Delta A â€” IDE-opened file context injection (~30 LOC, 1 file)**

File: `src/context.rs` (or `src/prompt.rs`, wherever the system-prompt builder lives).

```rust
pub fn render_ide_context(ide_state: &IdeState) -> Option<String> {
    if ide_state.active_file.is_none() && ide_state.recent_files.is_empty() {
        return None;
    }
    let mut out = String::new();
    if let Some(path) = &ide_state.active_file {
        writeln!(out, r#"<ide_opened_file path="{path}" active="true"/>"#).ok();
    }
    for path in ide_state.recent_files.iter().skip(1).take(5) {
        writeln!(out, r#"<ide_opened_file path="{path}"/>"#).ok();
    }
    Some(out)
}
```

Call site: `build_system_prompt` reads `AcpServer::ide_state()` (acp.rs:477) and appends the block AFTER the main system prompt body but BEFORE any cache-break marker, so re-renders on file-switch don't bust the cache. Wire it via an injected `&IdeState` argument; default to empty `IdeState::default()` for non-ACP entry points.

Test: assemble a prompt with `IdeState { active_file: Some("/a.rs"), recent_files: vec!["/a.rs", "/b.rs"], .. }` and assert both tags appear, active first.

**Delta B â€” task_notification system messages (~50 LOC in subagent.rs)**

CC's wire format (from cli/print.ts): system messages with `subtype: "task_notification"` containing `<status>Started</status>` or `<status>Completed</status>` plus the task description.

Add to `src/subagent.rs:run_subagent`:
1. At spawn (right after `register_with_id`): inject a message with role `system`, content `<task_notification><status>Started</status><task>{task}</task></task_notification>`, store into the transcript via the existing `store_transcript` path.
2. At completion (before returning `SubagentResult`): inject the same shape with `<status>Completed</status><result>{summary}</result>`.

Make the summary the first 200 chars of `result.final_text` so the parent transcript reads naturally.

Test (extend `src/subagent.rs` test module around line 2589): drive `run_subagent` with a mocked `client`, assert the persisted transcript starts with a `Started` task_notification and ends with `Completed`.

**Order of work:** Delta A is independently shippable today since #517 already landed. Delta B should wait for Phase 2 of #507 so the same emission path serves both single-subagent and coordinator-dispatched runs.

Closing the umbrella â€” both deltas are small enough to file as direct PR-sized issues when picked up.
